Welcome To Zambia Of Africa 🇿🇲 
We Now Have Our Own Wild Life Safari 🦒🦓🐘. 

Visit My Story To Check Out The wild Life 😳😳😳😳

Just when you thought we came to Africa 🇹🇿to enjoy a nice vacation, @srt_heather and I are actually showing a local detailing center how well our products really work. 

Check out @alpha.autospa in Tanzania Of Africa using our @nicksprofessionalsupplies Products to keep their customers cars in the greatest condition. After demonstrating our products the owner of the carwash was ready to purchase a HUGE order of supplies. 

This is what you call taking marketing to the Extreme Level. While packing my bags at home @srt_heather said make sure you bring products with us so that we can introduce Nicks To the detailing industry of Africa. 🇹🇿🇹🇿🇹🇿🇹🇿

node.text: Maasai warriors. They protect their tribe, their cattle and their grazing lands. Maasai have been known for centuries as fearsome hunters and warriors. Most Maasai wear the color red because it symbolizes their culture and they believe it scares away lions and it also symbolizes power.Also, most of the men wear a shuka, which is a red robe. They are the most friendliest and the most welcoming People. 🇹🇿

node.text:
Are Wishing To Have. I’m extremely happy to experience the journey coming to Africa and seeing how families are really living. 

The things that I don’t have doesn’t even matter anymore because I’m truly grateful for the things God Has Blessed Me With🙏🏿🙏🏿

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Shaquille Hinkson on August 21, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, bicycle and outdoors.

node.text:
Nothing Beats This Experience… 🇹🇿

Growing up as a kid I’ve always wanted to take a trip to Africa to Experience how life is on the other side of the world. 

Im happy I was able to put a smile on someone’s face today. Sometimes we don’t even realize how much you can make someone’s day better just by giving them a hug. ❤️

#africa #africanfood #africandance #áfrica #african #africaculture #africanprint #africanfashion #love
